==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: actinomycin
<hw>actinomycin</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <ets>actinomyces</ets>,
the genus of the organism in which they were first found.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>any of various red antibiotics isolated from soil
bacteria with a three-ring heterocyclic nucleus with an attached peptide
chain.</def> <note>Actinomycin D is the most well-known and has been
used to treat certain tumors. They act by binding to DNA and inhibiting
the transcription of RNA. Their binding to DNA has been much
studied.</note>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> actinomycin</syn> <stype>actinomycin C</stype>
<stype>actinomycin F<subs>1</subs></stype> <stype>actinomycin
D</stype>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>actinomycin D</ent>⟦br⟧
